modules.description: Provides functions to inline test cases directly within code using custom syntax extensions. Works with OCaml's test framework by generating test skeletons from annotated expressions. Enables quick validation of code snippets during development by embedding assertions and test outcomes inline.

Provides functions to process and transform OCaml AST expressions, including dropping test cases based on a flag, extracting test names and expressions, and expanding test structures. Works with OCaml AST nodes, location data, and attribute annotations. Used to inline test cases into the code during preprocessing, enabling conditional test execution.

Adds a test case with a specified path and name, executing a provided function that performs assertions. Operates on strings for test paths and names, and functions that take no arguments and return no value. Used to define and execute inline tests within a program's execution flow.
